he would go into the corner

21:21.482 --> 21:23.440
-and start sobbing and, um...
-LARRY CROMPTON: Yes.

21:23.524 --> 21:26.232
He would say,
"Bonnie is gonna hate me,"

21:26.315 --> 21:28.315
-or that type of thing.
-MICHELLE: Yeah.

21:28.399 --> 21:31.065
That must have just been
some kind of thing with him.

21:31.148 --> 21:32.440
CROMPTON: Yeah.

21:32.524 --> 21:34.565
MICHELLE: And I don't even know
what that could be, but yeah.

21:40.857 --> 21:43.065
I read about a case every day
that's solved by DNA

21:43.148 --> 21:45.482
and it's just some guy
who just is living quietly

21:45.565 --> 21:47.232
for the last 25 years
of his life,

21:47.315 --> 21:49.732
he met some woman that liked him
and had ki--

21:49.816 --> 21:51.816
you know, I would--
I just won't be surprised

21:51.899 --> 21:55.107
if it turns out, um,
that he's compartmentalized

21:55.190 --> 21:56.816
this part of his life
or something.

22:02.023 --> 22:04.107
MARY RITA SKRINE:
Oh, hey, Mish. It's Mary Rita.

22:04.190 --> 22:05.982
We're flying into LA so, um,

22:06.065 --> 22:07.941
wanted to see
if you guys were around.

22:08.023 --> 22:09.857
So just call me whenever.

22:09.941 --> 22:11.357
Thanks. Bye.

22:13.732 --> 22:15.482
In March,
I took my two kids

22:15.565 --> 22:16.941
to LA for spring break.

22:17.023 --> 22:21.273
And she was so excited
that we were there.

22:21.357 --> 22:23.232
First, she got the 23andMe.

22:23.315 --> 22:25.399
She's talking about our DNA.
(LAUGHS)

22:25.482 --> 22:27.732
And she was so excited.
And she's going through her--

22:27.816 --> 22:32.482
all the results and telling
my kids about everything.

22:32.565 --> 22:34.315
MICHELLE:
You guys know what 23andMe is?

22:34.399 --> 22:35.774
-MAN: Mm-hmm.
-MICHELLE: Okay.

22:35.857 --> 22:37.315
I did it like four years ago.

22:37.399 --> 22:39.524
I get an email
about every week that says,

22:39.607 --> 22:42.148
"Hey, we found
your second cousin.

22:42.232 --> 22:43.399
We found..." whatever.

22:43.482 --> 22:46.524
The chances that someone
in his greater family are--

22:46.607 --> 22:48.941
is in 23andMe is pretty high.

22:50.273 --> 22:51.941
So, she started
to talk about the case,

22:52.023 --> 22:54.482
and she said, "You guys want
to see the boxes?"

22:54.565 --> 22:57.941
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:59.107 --> 23:01.857
She just poured out
all these...

23:01.941 --> 23:03.315
details about the case

23:03.399 --> 23:06.273
and how excited she was,

23:06.357 --> 23:09.899
and all you did was hope
that she could solve it.

23:16.482 --> 23:20.649
I remember her
slowing down the writing,

23:20.732 --> 23:22.565
because she couldn't write

23:22.649 --> 23:25.440
until she went through
all of this stuff.

23:28.524 --> 23:31.357
And I'm not sure
if I heard from her again

23:32.273 --> 23:33.357
after that.

23:35.482 --> 23:40.482
Every available hour
from late January of 2016

23:40.565 --> 23:43.565
until April 21, 2016, was spent

23:43.649 --> 23:47.649
reviewing or interacting with
our new acquisition.

23:47.732 --> 23:50.107
The motherlode.

23:50.190 --> 23:53.440
MICHELLE: It's beyond
a treasure trove of info.

23:53.524 --> 23:56.607
I have to think there's at least
an 80 percent chance

23:56.691 --> 23:59.399
his name is buried
in here somewhere.

23:59.482 --> 24:01.065
HAYNES: We were following ideas

24:01.148 --> 24:04.232
and suspects
and theories and leads

24:04.315 --> 24:06.315
or, uh,
she would spot something

24:06.399 --> 24:08.399
that wasn't
thoroughly investigated

24:08.482 --> 24:09.857
or not followed up on.

24:12.315 --> 24:13.732
There was material in there

24:13.816 --> 24:16.691
that us other investigators
had never seen.

24:17.982 --> 24:21.607
And so,
as she came across material

24:21.691 --> 24:24.357
that she thought was relevant,
she did share that.

24:36.899 --> 24:40.023
So now,
I'm looking at who this guy is.

24:42.691 --> 24:45.107
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

24:49.273 --> 24:51.774
And I told Michelle,
"Yeah, you know, right now,

24:51.857 --> 24:55.107
I can't eliminate him, at all."

24:55.190 --> 24:57.565
So, Michelle was saying,
"We gotta get his DNA."

24:57.649 --> 24:59.065
I was like, "Absolutely."

25:08.565 --> 25:09.774
MELANIE: I can't even tell you,

25:09.857 --> 25:12.857
when you see something
that you're looking for,

25:12.941 --> 25:16.148
how far down
the rabbit hole you go.

25:16.232 --> 25:18.691
I mean, I can't believe
some of the things I've done,

25:18.774 --> 25:20.899
to tell you the truth.
(CHUCKLES)

25:26.607 --> 25:28.148
MICHELLE: Have you ever
interacted with anyone

25:28.232 --> 25:29.607
that you thought
might be a suspect, like...?

25:29.691 --> 25:32.691
MELANIE: Yes, I actually got DNA
on the suspect.

25:32.774 --> 25:34.440
MICHELLE:
You-- You yourself did?

25:34.524 --> 25:36.524
MELANIE:
Yes, and I know the suspect.

25:36.607 --> 25:37.691
MICHELLE: Oh my gosh.

25:37.774 --> 25:38.941
'Cause he was someone who, like,

25:39.023 --> 25:40.482
you went to high school with
or something?

25:40.565 --> 25:42.607
-MELANIE: I dated him.
-MICHELLE: Wow.

25:44.732 --> 25:46.148
MELANIE:
I happened to know a guy

25:46.232 --> 25:48.148
who was on the suspect list

25:48.232 --> 25:51.107
and I talked him into coming
into Sacramento.

25:52.732 --> 25:54.190
And so we have lunch.

25:54.273 --> 25:56.357
I'm thinking I'm gonna
bag the silverware,

25:56.440 --> 25:58.357
but I'm like,
I can't get the silverware

25:58.440 --> 26:00.607
without him seeing me.

26:00.691 --> 26:03.774
So, I say, "Well, why don't you
let me drive you home?"

26:05.941 --> 26:08.899
And so, I put him in the car,
and he had a bottle of water.

26:08.982 --> 26:11.607
And I go, "Can I have
the last sip of that water?"

26:11.691 --> 26:13.065
And I took it and kept it

26:13.148 --> 26:15.857
and turned it in
to be DNA tested.

26:15.941 --> 26:19.649
MICHELLE: Wow.
Did he live in any of the areas?

26:19.982 --> 26:21.607
MELANIE:

26:21.691 --> 26:23.315
MICHELLE: Oh, my gosh!

26:25.649 --> 26:26.941
MELANIE: Um...

26:29.691 --> 26:31.732
Yeah, I spend
three to four hours a day

26:31.816 --> 26:33.440
on this case.

26:33.524 --> 26:35.232
-I have five kids.
-MICHELLE: Right.

26:35.315 --> 26:37.524
MELANIE: My sixth grandchild
is due any second,

26:37.607 --> 26:40.399
and, um, I mean,
I just have a really full life,

26:40.482 --> 26:42.649
but I'm consumed with this case.

26:45.941 --> 26:47.816
MICHELLE: I've had
an uneasy realization

26:47.899 --> 26:50.148
about how our frenetic searching

26:50.232 --> 26:54.482
mirrors the compulsive behavior
of the one we seek.

26:55.399 --> 26:57.440
The trampled flower beds.

26:57.524 --> 27:00.107
Scratch marks on window screens.

27:00.190 --> 27:02.440
-Crank calls.
-(STATIC CRACKLES)

27:02.524 --> 27:05.524
We glimpse the rough outline
of what we seek,

27:05.607 --> 27:07.482
and we get snagged on it,

27:07.565 --> 27:09.565
sometimes remaining stuck

27:09.649 --> 27:12.023
when we could get free
and move on.

27:16.482 --> 27:17.816
-My song--
-MICHELLE: Wait, wait, wait.

27:17.899 --> 27:18.774
One, two, three.

27:18.857 --> 27:21.357
This is my song
that I want to show you.

27:22.482 --> 27:25.065
That I learned from, uh...

27:25.148 --> 27:27.357
♪ (PIANO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

27:27.440 --> 27:28.649
