MICHELLE: The interesting thing
about Janelle's case

32:34.482 --> 32:37.023
is the gap
between '81 and '86.

32:39.691 --> 32:43.107
He obviously was stopping
for whatever reason.

32:43.190 --> 32:44.691
(ENGINE REVVING)

32:44.774 --> 32:46.107
It wasn't just
that he saw Janelle

32:46.190 --> 32:47.273
and was like,
"I'm gonna kill her."

32:47.357 --> 32:48.899
I think there was a combination
of, like,

32:48.982 --> 32:50.482
she was gonna be
his next victim,

32:50.565 --> 32:53.774
and I think it must've been some
sort of precipitating stressor,

32:53.857 --> 32:55.816
and who knows what that was.

32:55.899 --> 32:58.524
Maybe he just got kicked out
of his house or something,

32:58.607 --> 33:00.232
you know, lost his job.

33:00.315 --> 33:04.357
He was just obviously
very, very angry.

33:06.816 --> 33:11.399
And, yeah, it's just--
it's-- it's-- it's just a very,

33:12.148 --> 33:14.399
very sad story, and, um...

33:14.482 --> 33:19.065
and you can just only hope
that somehow, in her life--

33:19.148 --> 33:22.315
like in that time period
around when she died,

33:22.399 --> 33:24.107
maybe there is a clue
of, you know,

33:24.190 --> 33:26.273
maybe she--
something she said or...

33:26.357 --> 33:28.857
So, you know, looking
into her life in that way

33:28.941 --> 33:30.565
is interesting to me, yeah.

33:30.649 --> 33:33.816
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

