35:15.107 --> 35:17.941
Each time, I look dazed,

35:18.023 --> 35:19.732
slightly wide-eyed,

35:19.816 --> 35:23.816
as if I'm seeing something
unbelievable for the first time.

35:34.607 --> 35:36.857
The neediness
of his stubby fingers

35:36.941 --> 35:39.023
digging inside me.

35:39.107 --> 35:41.190
The scene in Linen Hall Library,

35:41.273 --> 35:43.816
burning eyes staring at me.

35:45.190 --> 35:48.565
(WAVES CRASHING)

35:49.649 --> 35:52.107
(READS)

36:01.190 --> 36:02.732
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

36:03.107 --> 36:05.065
(READS)

36:13.524 --> 36:17.982
The conversation with Mom
and Dad really tore me apart.

36:18.065 --> 36:21.941
I know they care immensely
and want what's best for me.

36:22.023 --> 36:23.399
I just think sometimes,

36:23.482 --> 36:26.232
they don't know
what's going on inside me.

36:30.023 --> 36:31.982
I'm so angry, and then I'm not.

36:32.065 --> 36:35.357
I'm so sad
and full of self-doubt,

36:35.440 --> 36:37.357
and then I'm not.

36:37.440 --> 36:41.649
Where...
Where can this all lead?

36:57.816 --> 36:59.607
GAY HARDWICK: A year
and a few months past,

36:59.691 --> 37:03.399
uh, the attack,
we had sold the house.

37:03.482 --> 37:06.982
And we decided to get married
in the backyard of--

37:07.065 --> 37:10.774
of the new house
when the landscaping was put in.

37:12.357 --> 37:14.232
So, we just had a small wedding,

37:14.315 --> 37:19.065
with just a few close family
and friends. (CHUCKLES)

37:19.148 --> 37:23.232
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

37:23.315 --> 37:27.232
Bob is huge on moving forward
and moving on.

37:27.315 --> 37:30.899
And that was good for me
to have somebody to grab my hand

37:30.982 --> 37:32.982
and say
we were gonna move forward,

37:33.065 --> 37:34.941
and we were gonna move
past this

37:35.023 --> 37:39.148
and we were not gonna let it
destroy our life.

37:43.649 --> 37:47.649
On the other hand,
I actually had been suffering

37:47.732 --> 37:50.273
a lot of post-traumatic
stress symptoms.

37:51.482 --> 37:54.982
I just was afraid
and exhausted all the time,

37:56.524 --> 38:00.565
but I wasn't formally diagnosed
for about six years.

38:02.273 --> 38:04.065
And the psychiatrist said,

38:04.148 --> 38:07.148
you know,
my central nervous system has--

38:07.232 --> 38:10.232
has been rewired
because of the trauma

38:10.315 --> 38:12.899
that I experienced
during those hours.

38:12.982 --> 38:17.065
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

38:17.857 --> 38:20.982
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

38:39.482 --> 38:42.732
You don't live your life
the same way again, ever.

38:45.440 --> 38:47.440
Um...

38:47.524 --> 38:50.107
you know, I'm sure you've had
your times of depression,

38:50.190 --> 38:53.649
but you handle it
much better than me.

38:53.732 --> 38:56.315
I wouldn't say that.
I just handle it differently.

38:56.399 --> 38:58.565
I remember in a mediation,

38:59.816 --> 39:02.065
a-- a attorney called
my client a liar,

39:02.148 --> 39:05.565
and it was in a court mediation
and I just flipped out.

39:05.649 --> 39:07.774
I just stood up and pinned
the guy against the wall.

39:07.857 --> 39:09.065
(CHUCKLES)

39:09.148 --> 39:13.315
I guess, then I was in--
I felt maybe I was in control.

39:13.399 --> 39:15.607
But when you think
about what she went through,

39:15.691 --> 39:17.899
she went through
a lot more than I went through

39:17.982 --> 39:19.399
and then it's--
uh, but the bad part

39:19.482 --> 39:21.357
is I could do nothing about it,
you know.

39:21.440 --> 39:23.190
That's the--
That's the only thing.

39:23.273 --> 39:24.315
That's...

39:26.232 --> 39:27.857
But I still think about it,
you know.

39:27.941 --> 39:29.899
You know, you want
to protect your wife,

39:29.982 --> 39:32.774
you want to protect your kids,
but sometimes you can't.

39:34.148 --> 39:36.982
Well, for, you know--
you may have those feelings,

39:37.065 --> 39:40.524
but in the past 40 years,
you've more than made up...

39:40.607 --> 39:45.607
(LAUGHS) ...for-- for taking,
you know, extra care of me

39:45.691 --> 39:50.941
at times when I'm sure other men
probably would've walked away.

39:54.273 --> 39:55.440
So...

39:55.524 --> 39:59.273
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

40:01.524 --> 40:04.190
You learn to live
with these things

40:04.273 --> 40:08.357
just like you learn to live
with the loss of a loved one,

40:08.440 --> 40:12.691
and you pass through stages
and hopefully you recover.

40:12.774 --> 40:15.190
And you become
a fully functioning human being

40:15.273 --> 40:16.649
with a happy life.

40:18.232 --> 40:20.691
BOB HARDWICK: I mean, I wanted
to be super wealthy one day

40:20.774 --> 40:23.315
and she wanted to be the top
of a construction company

40:23.399 --> 40:26.232
and we just decided
that we could start a family

40:26.315 --> 40:27.857
and, you know,
take a different approach.

40:29.065 --> 40:33.691
GAY: So we dialed back
and I stayed home ten years.

40:36.691 --> 40:40.315
So, we started out with one,
and it grew to three.

40:40.399 --> 40:43.357
And finally, to four.
Family of six.

40:46.190 --> 40:47.982
And, uh, all the kids

40:48.065 --> 40:50.857
have brought
great gifts to our lives.

40:59.691 --> 41:02.065
MARY RITA:
Happy birthday, sweet sister.

41:02.148 --> 41:03.941
I hope you're having a good day.

41:04.023 --> 41:05.857
MARGO CHADWICK:
Hey, Mish. It's Margo.

41:05.941 --> 41:08.232
Calling to wish you
a very happy birthday.

41:08.315 --> 41:10.190
I love ya.
Hope everything's going well.

41:10.273 --> 41:11.941
PATRICK SKRINE: Hey,
Aunt Michelle. It's Patrick.

41:12.023 --> 41:14.148
I just wanted to say
happy birthday to you.

41:14.232 --> 41:16.440
ADAM DRUCKER:
Happy birthday, beautiful.

41:16.524 --> 41:18.107
And I hope you're having
a great night

41:18.190 --> 41:20.357
doing something fun
with your family.

41:20.440 --> 41:22.440
I love you
very, very, very much.

41:22.524 --> 41:24.273
Bye, baby.

