42:44.649 --> 42:47.691
MICHELLE: Little Dom's
and old police files.

42:47.774 --> 42:49.899
Miss you guys so much.

42:49.982 --> 42:52.315
Remember to tell Alice
Mommy loves her

42:52.399 --> 42:54.565
and can't wait to be finished
with her book,

42:54.649 --> 42:57.982
so that I can be with her more
than she'll ever want me to be.

43:01.190 --> 43:02.857
PATTON: That can really pull you

43:02.941 --> 43:05.649
into some depths that you can't
get yourself back out of.

43:15.440 --> 43:17.440
MICHELLE: Holy mother of God.

43:18.691 --> 43:22.315
I came across a shitload
of photos in my boxes.

43:23.315 --> 43:25.440
A whole shoebox full.

43:26.899 --> 43:28.649
Fucking monster.

43:30.190 --> 43:33.023
I'd never seen
the Smith scene in Ventura.

43:33.857 --> 43:35.023
Bludgeoned with a log

43:35.107 --> 43:37.691
from firewood pile
outside house.

43:38.524 --> 43:40.065
Bark everywhere.

43:42.524 --> 43:44.524
But I will say,
crime scene wise,

43:44.607 --> 43:49.524
there is something very striking
about how eerily similar

43:49.607 --> 43:51.691
the individual crime scenes are.

43:59.732 --> 44:01.982
There's something so, um...

44:03.607 --> 44:05.941
uh, I can't-- I wish
I could articulate it,

44:06.023 --> 44:09.691
the way he-- he walks
around people's houses

44:11.524 --> 44:14.023
and the way he destroys them.

44:15.065 --> 44:17.691
And sort of hangs out and eats.

44:19.941 --> 44:22.440
That's why I just don't think
this is like pure sexual sadism.

44:22.524 --> 44:24.148
I think
there was something else,

44:24.232 --> 44:26.732
you know,
going on there psychologically.

44:37.565 --> 44:43.482
It's so, um, king-- "I am king"
and how, you know, this is--

44:43.565 --> 44:46.399
He just-- it's so--
it's so unusual to have someone

44:46.482 --> 44:49.065
who just actually wants
to ruin your home,

44:49.148 --> 44:51.482
where it's like so--
it's like he got

44:51.565 --> 44:53.899
to the emotional center
of people's lives

44:54.023 --> 44:56.440
and just wanted to destroy that.

45:00.107 --> 45:03.065
PATTON: (YAWNS)
Hey, it's, uh, it's Patton.

45:03.148 --> 45:05.607
Try to call me in, like,
uh, ten minutes

45:05.691 --> 45:07.774
'cause I'm kinda
falling asleep here.

45:07.857 --> 45:09.440
I'd love to talk to you.

45:11.482 --> 45:14.440
MICHELLE: (READS)

45:24.941 --> 45:27.982
PATTON: It was a lot
of sleeplessness and insomnia.

45:28.065 --> 45:30.190
There must have been days
where she was, like,

45:30.273 --> 45:31.565
"I'll take Adderall
in the morning.

45:31.649 --> 45:33.816
I'll take, you know, Xanax
and Vicodin to get to sleep

45:33.899 --> 45:35.691
because I'm--
this is for a better--

45:35.774 --> 45:37.816
this is for a bigger purpose
than me."

45:38.482 --> 45:41.065
(TAPE RECORDER REWINDS)

45:41.148 --> 45:43.399
DREW WITTHUHN: But if you wanna
just run through, I...

45:43.482 --> 45:46.065
-I don't mind.
-MICHELLE: Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah.
No, totally. Yeah.

45:46.148 --> 45:48.607
DREW:
So, uh, the night before

45:48.691 --> 45:50.232
CSI released the house...

45:50.315 --> 45:51.565
MICHELLE: Mm-hmm.

45:51.649 --> 45:54.607
DREW: ...I really wasn't allowed
to get anywhere near it.

45:54.691 --> 45:55.816
MICHELLE: Right.

45:56.607 --> 45:58.023
DREW:

45:59.107 --> 46:00.482
Um, they called and said, "Okay,

46:00.565 --> 46:01.857
you know,
we're releasing the home,

46:01.941 --> 46:06.107
so now you guys can go in
and-- and basically clean up.

46:06.190 --> 46:08.816
Because at the time,
they didn't have companies

46:08.899 --> 46:10.732
that specialized in crime scenes

46:10.816 --> 46:13.607
and-- and biohazard things
and things like that.

46:13.691 --> 46:16.273
And I felt a responsibility
to my brother

46:16.357 --> 46:19.273
to make this crime scene
no longer a crime scene.

46:19.357 --> 46:21.148
Let's turn it back into a home.

46:23.482 --> 46:25.482
-DREW: And, uh...
-MICHELLE:

46:25.565 --> 46:27.732
DREW:

46:27.816 --> 46:29.023
MICHELLE: Oh, wow.

46:29.524 --> 46:31.190
(DOOR CREAKING)

46:35.982 --> 46:38.273
DREW: We went into the bedroom
and took a look around,

46:38.357 --> 46:40.941
and it wasn't a pretty sight.

46:41.023 --> 46:42.649
You know,
it's not the kinda thing

46:42.732 --> 46:44.816
you want to remember
if you don't have to.

46:48.524 --> 46:50.524
He had a very intricate
brass bed,

46:50.607 --> 46:54.107
which took a long time to clean
because there was,

46:54.190 --> 46:56.565
you know,
blood spatter everywhere.

46:56.649 --> 46:59.899
And on the carpet
and the wall behind it.

47:11.732 --> 47:12.857
MICHELLE: Mm-hmm.

47:12.941 --> 47:15.482
DREW: And we cleaned it up
as well as we could.

47:15.565 --> 47:17.482
MICHELLE: And this is before
David has seen it.

47:17.565 --> 47:20.565
So, yeah, you're protecting
him from it, yeah. Yeah. Yeah.

47:24.732 --> 47:26.482
DREW: When we finally left
the house

47:26.565 --> 47:28.732
and everything was done,

47:28.816 --> 47:32.148
the autopilot was almost
turned off, if that makes sense.

47:32.232 --> 47:36.190
And the rush of emotion,
it just overwhelmed me.

47:38.732 --> 47:42.148
My thoughts were of my brother
and of my sister-in-law.

47:43.732 --> 47:46.148
And I have no idea why,
to this day I don't,

47:46.232 --> 47:48.899
but at that very moment,
I mourned for my dad.

47:58.941 --> 48:01.148
MICHELLE: Wow. Oh, my gosh.

48:01.524 --> 48:03.440
DREW:

48:03.524 --> 48:05.607
-And he...
-MICHELLE:

48:05.691 --> 48:07.273
DREW: You know, it's one
of those things, and I--

48:07.357 --> 48:08.982
It's hard to say.
We really don't know.

48:09.065 --> 48:10.440
-MICHELLE: Yeah, yeah.
-DREW: But, um,

48:10.524 --> 48:13.774
it kinda all hit us
like a ton of bricks, obviously.

48:26.482 --> 48:28.190
-MICHELLE: Yeah.
